 :tx/rationale "ADR-024 OBSERVATION 16: RATE-DISTORTION CONNECTION. The optimal encoding of the store into the LLM's context window at a given budget is characterized by the rate-distortion function R(D). Rate = budget (tokens or bits). Distortion = divergence between LLM's post-reading understanding and store's actual state. Our attention scoring (surprisal × relevance × actionability) is an approximation of the optimal rate-distortion encoder. The rate-distortion theorem guarantees an achievable lower bound on distortion at any rate — the attention budget should converge toward that bound as calibration data accumulates. This connects the attention budget to Shannon's foundational information theory and provides a theoretical justification for the surprisal decay rate: it should match the channel's capacity characteristic, not be arbitrarily chosen."
